-- Factbox: U.S. midsize cars
-- 
-- Fri Sep 21, 2012 2:14pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/09/21/us-autos-familysedans-idUSBRE88K10P20120921

 

 (Reuters) - The six best-selling cars in the midsize sector include brands from the United States, Japan and Korea. Together, they account for 55 percent of total U.S. midsize sales. Their cumulative sales through August: 
 * Toyota Camry	280,536 * Honda Accord	218,665 * Nissan Altima	209,592 * Ford Fusion	181,865 * Chevrolet Malibu 168,277 * Hyundai Sonata 158,014 Source: Autodata Corp (Reporting By Paul Lienert in Detroit)